docs.lead_paragraph: Heavy buying of the Canadian dollar last week propelled it to another new high premium in terms of American, when it sold at 3 11/16 cent, unmatched since September, 1934. Week's lowest was 2 11/16 cent, made on Monday, and Thursday's final of 3 9/16 cent, reflected a gain of 31/32 cent over the previous week.

docs.lead_paragraph: AS every Argentine schoolboy, and nearly every Latin-American schoolboy, once knew, Gainza Paz is the man who was most instrumental in making La Prensa the foremost Latin-American newspaper. In the recently published "Defense of Freedom," Senor Gainza, along with his co-editors, tells the story of the paper's struggles and triumphs up through that fatal day early in 1951, when a dictator ordered its presses stopped.
